  "text": "The natural nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide (NAD) + precursor and NAD + -dependent enzyme inhibitor nicotinamide (NAM) has been recently shown to induce a 60-to 80-fold NK-cell expansion when added to feeder-free cultures containing IL-2 and IL-15 [CITATION_1] . In this study, NAM also affected NK cell anti-tumor capabilities and trafficking properties by modulating expression of CD200R and PD1, two immune regulatory receptors that transmit inhibitory signals upon interaction with cognate ligands on cancer cells. In addition, NAM promoted surface expression of L-selectin, an adhesion molecule mediating interactions with vascular endothelium and lymph nodes.",
